IC.BUS.DFRN.XQ-fv.def: Distance to frontier score illustrates the distance of an economy to the "frontier," which represents the best performance observed on each Doing Business topic across all economies and years included since 2005. An economy's distance to frontier is indicated on a scale from 0 to 100, where 0 represents the lowest performance and 100 the frontier. For example, a score of 75 in 2012 means an economy was 25 percentage points away from the frontier constructed from the best performances across all economies and across time. A score of 80 in 2013 would indicate the economy is improving.
IC.BUS.DFRN.XQ-fv.name: Distance to frontier score

IC.BUS.DISC.XQ-fv.def: Disclosure index measures the extent to which investors are protected through disclosure of ownership and financial information. The index ranges from 0 to 10, with higher values indicating more disclosure.
IC.BUS.DISC.XQ-fv.name: Business extent of disclosure index

IC.BUS.EASE.XQ-fv.def: Ease of doing business ranks economies from 1 to 190, with first place being the best. A high ranking (a low numerical rank) means that the regulatory environment is conducive to business operation. The index averages the country's percentile rankings on 10 topics covered in the World Bank's Doing Business. The ranking on each topic is the simple average of the percentile rankings on its component indicators.
IC.BUS.EASE.XQ-fv.name: Ease of doing business index

IC.BUS.NDNS.ZS-fv.def: New businesses registered are the number of new limited liability corporations registered in the calendar year.
IC.BUS.NDNS.ZS-fv.name: New business density
IC.BUS.NDNS.ZS-fv.source: World Bank's Entrepreneurship Survey and database (http://www.doingbusiness.org/data/exploretopics/entrepreneurship).

IC.BUS.NREG-fv.def: New businesses registered are the number of new limited liability corporations registered in the calendar year.
IC.BUS.NREG-fv.name: New businesses registered
IC.BUS.NREG-fv.source: World Bank's Entrepreneurship Survey and database (http://www.doingbusiness.org/data/exploretopics/entrepreneurship).

IC.CRD.INFO.XQ-fv.def: Depth of credit information index measures rules affecting the scope, accessibility, and quality of credit information available through public or private credit registries. The index ranges from 0 to 8, with higher values indicating the availability of more credit information, from either a public registry or a private bureau, to facilitate lending decisions.
IC.CRD.INFO.XQ-fv.name: Depth of credit information index

IC.CRD.PRVT.ZS-fv.def: Private credit bureau coverage reports the number of individuals or firms listed by a private credit bureau with current information on repayment history, unpaid debts, or credit outstanding. The number is expressed as a percentage of the adult population.
IC.CRD.PRVT.ZS-fv.name: Private credit bureau coverage

IC.CRD.PUBL.ZS-fv.def: Public credit registry coverage reports the number of individuals and firms listed in a public credit registry with current information on repayment history, unpaid debts, or credit outstanding. The number is expressed as a percentage of the adult population.
IC.CRD.PUBL.ZS-fv.name: Public credit registry coverage

IC.CUS.DURS.EX-fv.def: Average time to clear exports through customs is the average number of days to clear direct exports through customs.
IC.CUS.DURS.EX-fv.name: Average time to clear exports through customs

IC.ELC.DURS-fv.def: The average wait, in days, experienced to obtain an electrical connection from the day an establishment applies for it to the day it receives the service.
IC.ELC.DURS-fv.name: Time to obtain an electrical connection

IC.ELC.OUTG-fv.def: Power outages are the average number of power outages that establishments experience in a typical month.
IC.ELC.OUTG-fv.name: Power outages in firms in a typical month

IC.ELC.OUTG.ZS-fv.def: Percent of firms experiencing electrical outages during the previous fiscal year.
IC.ELC.OUTG.ZS-fv.name: Firms experiencing electrical outages

IC.ELC.TIME-fv.def: Time required to get electricity is the number of days to obtain a permanent electricity connection. The measure captures the median duration that the electricity utility and experts indicate is necessary in practice, rather than required by law, to complete a procedure.
IC.ELC.TIME-fv.name: Time required to get electricity

IC.FRM.BKWC.ZS-fv.def: Firms using banks to finance working capital are the percentage of firms using bank loans to finance working capital.
IC.FRM.BKWC.ZS-fv.name: Firms using banks to finance working capital

IC.FRM.BNKS.ZS-fv.def: Firms using banks to finance investment are the percentage of firms using banks to finance investments.
IC.FRM.BNKS.ZS-fv.name: Firms using banks to finance investment

IC.FRM.BRIB.ZS-fv.def: Bribery incidence is the percentage of firms experiencing at least one bribe payment request across 6 public transactions dealing with utilities access, permits, licenses, and taxes.
IC.FRM.BRIB.ZS-fv.name: Bribery incidence
IC.FRM.BRIB.ZS-fv.units: % of firms experiencing at least one bribe payment request

IC.FRM.CMPU.ZS-fv.def: Firms competing against unregistered firms are the percentage of firms competing against unregistered or informal firms.
IC.FRM.CMPU.ZS-fv.name: Firms competing against unregistered firms

IC.FRM.CORR.ZS-fv.def: Informal payments to public officials are the percentage of firms expected to make informal payments to public officials to "get things done" with regard to customs, taxes, licenses, regulations, services, and the like.
IC.FRM.CORR.ZS-fv.name: Informal payments to public officials

IC.FRM.CRIM.ZS-fv.def: Average losses as a result of theft, robbery, vandalism or arson that occurred on the establishment’s premises calculated as a percentage of annual sales. The value represents the average losses for all firms which reported losses (please see indicator IC.FRM.THEV.ZS).
IC.FRM.CRIM.ZS-fv.name: Losses due to theft and vandalism
IC.FRM.CRIM.ZS-fv.units: % of annual sales for affected firms

IC.FRM.DURS-fv.def: Time required to obtain operating license is the average wait to obtain an operating license from the day the establishment applied for it to the day it was granted.
IC.FRM.DURS-fv.name: Time required to obtain an operating license

IC.FRM.FEMM.ZS-fv.def: Firms with female top manager refers to the percentage of firms in the private sector who have females as top managers. Top manager refers to the highest ranking manager or CEO of the establishment. This person may be the owner if he/she works as the manager of the firm. The results are based on surveys of more than 100,000 private firms.
IC.FRM.FEMM.ZS-fv.name: Firms with female top manager

IC.FRM.FEMO.ZS-fv.def: Firms with female participation in ownership are the percentage of firms with a woman among the principal owners.
IC.FRM.FEMO.ZS-fv.name: Firms with female participation in ownership

IC.FRM.FREG.ZS-fv.def: Firms formally registered when operations started are the percentage of firms formally registered when they started operations in the country.
IC.FRM.FREG.ZS-fv.name: Firms formally registered when operations started

IC.FRM.INFM.ZS-fv.def: Firms that do not report all sales for tax purposes are the percentage of firms that expressed that a typical firm reports less than 100 percent of sales for tax purposes; such firms are termed "informal firms."
IC.FRM.INFM.ZS-fv.name: Firms that do not report all sales for tax purposes

IC.FRM.METG.ZS-fv.def: Percent of firms that were visited or required to meet with tax officials.
IC.FRM.METG.ZS-fv.name: Firms visited or required meetings with tax officials

IC.FRM.OUTG.ZS-fv.def: Average losses due to electrical outages, as percentage of total annual sales. The value represents average losses for all firms which reported outages (please see indicator IC.ELC.OUTG.ZS).
IC.FRM.OUTG.ZS-fv.name: Value lost due to electrical outages

IC.FRM.RSDV.ZS-fv.def: Percent of firms that spend on research and development.
IC.FRM.RSDV.ZS-fv.name: Firms that spend on R&D

IC.FRM.THEV.ZS-fv.def: Percent of firms experiencing losses due to theft, robbery, vandalism or arson that occurred on the establishment's premises.
IC.FRM.THEV.ZS-fv.name: Firms experiencing losses due to theft and vandalism

IC.FRM.TRNG.ZS-fv.def: Firms offering formal training are the percentage of firms offering formal training programs for their permanent, full-time employees.
IC.FRM.TRNG.ZS-fv.name: Firms offering formal training

IC.GOV.DURS.ZS-fv.def: Time spent dealing with the requirements of government regulations is the proportion of senior management's time, in a typical week, that is spent dealing with the requirements imposed by government regulations (e.g., taxes, customs, labor regulations, licensing and registration, including dealings with officials, and completing forms).
IC.GOV.DURS.ZS-fv.name: Time spent dealing with the requirements of government regulations

IC.ISV.DURS-fv.def: Time to resolve insolvency is the number of years from the filing for insolvency in court until the resolution of distressed assets.
IC.ISV.DURS-fv.name: Time to resolve insolvency

IC.LGL.CRED.XQ-fv.def: Strength of legal rights index measures the degree to which collateral and bankruptcy laws protect the rights of borrowers and lenders and thus facilitate lending. The index ranges from 0 to 12, with higher scores indicating that these laws are better designed to expand access to credit.
IC.LGL.CRED.XQ-fv.name: Strength of legal rights index

IC.LGL.DURS-fv.def: Time required to enforce a contract is the number of calendar days from the filing of the lawsuit in court until the final determination and, in appropriate cases, payment.
IC.LGL.DURS-fv.name: Time required to enforce a contract

IC.PRP.DURS-fv.def: Time required to register property is the number of calendar days needed for businesses to secure rights to property.
IC.PRP.DURS-fv.name: Time required to register property

IC.PRP.PROC-fv.def: Number of procedures to register property is the number of procedures required for a businesses to secure rights to property.
IC.PRP.PROC-fv.name: Procedures to register property

IC.REG.COST.PC.FE.ZS-fv.def: Cost to register a business is normalized by presenting it as a percentage of gross national income (GNI) per capita.
IC.REG.COST.PC.FE.ZS-fv.name: Cost of business start-up procedures

IC.REG.COST.PC.MA.ZS-fv.def: Cost to register a business is normalized by presenting it as a percentage of gross national income (GNI) per capita.
IC.REG.COST.PC.MA.ZS-fv.name: Cost of business start-up procedures

IC.REG.COST.PC.ZS-fv.def: Cost to register a business is normalized by presenting it as a percentage of gross national income (GNI) per capita.
IC.REG.COST.PC.ZS-fv.name: Cost of business start-up procedures

IC.REG.DURS-fv.def: Time required to start a business is the number of calendar days needed to complete the procedures to legally operate a business. If a procedure can be speeded up at additional cost, the fastest procedure, independent of cost, is chosen.
IC.REG.DURS-fv.name: Time required to start a business

IC.REG.DURS.FE-fv.def: Time required to start a business is the number of calendar days needed to complete the procedures to legally operate a business. If a procedure can be speeded up at additional cost, the fastest procedure, independent of cost, is chosen.
IC.REG.DURS.FE-fv.name: Time required to start a business

IC.REG.DURS.MA-fv.def: Time required to start a business is the number of calendar days needed to complete the procedures to legally operate a business. If a procedure can be speeded up at additional cost, the fastest procedure, independent of cost, is chosen.
IC.REG.DURS.MA-fv.name: Time required to start a business

IC.REG.PROC-fv.def: Start-up procedures are those required to start a business, including interactions to obtain necessary permits and licenses and to complete all inscriptions, verifications, and notifications to start operations. Data are for businesses with specific characteristics of ownership, size, and type of production.
IC.REG.PROC-fv.name: Start-up procedures to register a business

IC.REG.PROC.FE-fv.def: Start-up procedures are those required to start a business, including interactions to obtain necessary permits and licenses and to complete all inscriptions, verifications, and notifications to start operations. Data are for businesses with specific characteristics of ownership, size, and type of production.
IC.REG.PROC.FE-fv.name: Start-up procedures to register a business

IC.REG.PROC.MA-fv.def: Start-up procedures are those required to start a business, including interactions to obtain necessary permits and licenses and to complete all inscriptions, verifications, and notifications to start operations. Data are for businesses with specific characteristics of ownership, size, and type of production.
IC.REG.PROC.MA-fv.name: Start-up procedures to register a business

IC.TAX.DURS-fv.def: Time to prepare and pay taxes is the time, in hours per year, it takes to prepare, file, and pay (or withhold) three major types of taxes: the corporate income tax, the value added or sales tax, and labor taxes, including payroll taxes and social security contributions.
IC.TAX.DURS-fv.name: Time to prepare and pay taxes

IC.TAX.GIFT.ZS-fv.def: Firms expected to give gifts in meetings with tax officials is the percentage of firms that answered positively to the question "was a gift or informal payment expected or requested during a meeting with tax officials?"
IC.TAX.GIFT.ZS-fv.name: Firms expected to give gifts in meetings with tax officials

IC.TAX.LABR.CP.ZS-fv.def: Labor tax and contributions is the amount of taxes and mandatory contributions on labor paid by the business.
IC.TAX.LABR.CP.ZS-fv.name: Labor tax and contributions

IC.TAX.METG-fv.def: Average number of visits or required meetings with tax officials during the year. The value represents the average number of visits for all firms which reported being visited or required to meet with tax officials (please see indicator IC.FRM.METG.ZS).
IC.TAX.METG-fv.name: Number of visits or required meetings with tax officials

IC.TAX.OTHR.CP.ZS-fv.def: Other taxes payable by businesses include the amounts paid for property taxes, turnover taxes, and other small taxes such as municipal fees and vehicle and fuel taxes.
IC.TAX.OTHR.CP.ZS-fv.name: Other taxes payable by businesses

IC.TAX.PAYM-fv.def: Tax payments by businesses are the total number of taxes paid by businesses, including electronic filing. The tax is counted as paid once a year even if payments are more frequent.
IC.TAX.PAYM-fv.name: Tax payments

IC.TAX.PRFT.CP.ZS-fv.def: Profit tax is the amount of taxes on profits paid by the business.
IC.TAX.PRFT.CP.ZS-fv.name: Profit tax

IC.TAX.TOTL.CP.ZS-fv.def: Total tax rate measures the amount of taxes and mandatory contributions payable by businesses after accounting for allowable deductions and exemptions as a share of commercial profits. Taxes withheld (such as personal income tax) or collected and remitted to tax authorities (such as value added taxes, sales taxes or goods and service taxes) are excluded.
IC.TAX.TOTL.CP.ZS-fv.name: Total tax rate

IC.WRH.DURS-fv.def: Time required to build a warehouse is the number of calendar days needed to complete the required procedures for building a warehouse. If a procedure can be speeded up at additional cost, the fastest procedure, independent of cost, is chosen.
IC.WRH.DURS-fv.name: Time required to build a warehouse

IC.WRH.PROC-fv.def: Number of procedures to build a warehouse is the number of interactions of a company's employees or managers with external parties, including government agency staff, public inspectors, notaries, land registry and cadastre staff, and technical experts apart from architects and engineers.
IC.WRH.PROC-fv.name: Procedures to build a warehouse
